rest_of_day_open: I see it going okay. I have to go to work each day until Friday. I'm sure work will be stressful, I've got a lot of things to get done before the weekend. My birthday is Saturday, so it's likely I will take myself and my daughter out to eat.
critical_positive: We both got along very well. She was friendly and kind and an excellent listener. We laughed a lot. We realized we had many things in common, such as: growing up in small towns, our dislike of spiders, and lockdown. It was interesting to learn how in other parts of the United States things are being done.
critical_negative: She was quiet, though at the beginning she said she was low energy. It was a bit distracting she kept slurping coffee out of a large mug while we were speaking. She also kept fooling with her hair with is a pet peeve of mine, but probably something she was doing out of nervousness.

rest_of_day_open: It will probably be about the same as the previous week. A lot of rest and some house work. It will be ok but not amazing. I will be spending a lot of time at home, except for when I leave to go to appointments. I hope it will go ok.
critical_positive: I thought that she was nice to talk to and put in plenty of effort on her end of the conversation. We found things that we had in common to talk about and conversation did not lag too much. I did the best that I could on my end as well.
critical_negative: I wasn't always sure what to talk about and I felt pretty anxious, especially at the beginning of our conversation. I was also feeling very tired, which didn't help with the flow of conversation, even though I had coffee before and during. It wasn't through any fault of my conversation partner.
